reviewText: I've always dug Babyface. the Brother had the Smooth Slow Jams and he grew as a Solo Artist after writing and Producing for others and a whose who of Acts in the Industry. His videos were cool as well. Face always kept things on the smooth tip and he never sounded trendy as he was his own trend. a Good Solid collection here. Face has left a lasting mark.
Title: Baby Face - A Collection of Hit Videos

reviewText: ....Maximum 'Face in his more popular videos.Highlights of this great compilation include his MTV Unplugged duet with Eric Clapton, "Change the World", LL Cool J and Shalimar in "This is For The Lover In You", Stevie Wonder joining him for a ballad on the trials and tribulations of abuse and the original "Whip Appeal"...Keep an eye out for Holly Robinson, Michael Beach, Bobby Brown--with a then fashionable, now questionable Gumby haircut--his partna in high crime, LA Reid, and his beautiful wife.Note how "Its No Crime" and "Tender Lover" still appears flashy and colorful. Also, this helped me to pay attention to and seek out a copy of the great, underrated Face tune "Never Keeping Secrets"....
summary: This Is For the Cool Lover in You....
Title: Baby Face - A Collection of Hit Videos
